description: Available at: https://openstudionetwork.com/keezer - In this 2-part lesson, Geoffrey shows you how to create lush and contemporary minor voicings used by post-bebop pianists like Bill Evans and Herbie Hancock, by using clusters of "pretty notes" and inversions. Geoffrey demonstrates the "Bill Evans" 3-note voicing as well as sounds used by today's composers such as Maria Schneider, Wayne Shorter, Bob Brookmeyer and Bob Mintzer. (Level: Intermediate)
title: Geoffrey Keezer - Contemporary Minor Voicings (Preview)
